    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored by **Corbin Carroll**, who boasts our highest efficiency score of 85.94 today against Taijuan Walker. His elite speed is a major catalyst, and while we factor in a minor 2% penalty for Walker\u2019s 1.86s pop time, the combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and the prime #2 spot in the order makes him a cornerstone play. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) are high-ceiling starts against M\u00e1rquez and Fedde, respectively. Both benefit significantly from favorable pitching matchups and premium lineup placement\u2014specifically, **Mickey Moniak** gains an additional 5% boost from wind conditions and his #3 spot, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** exploits a plus-matchup against a pitcher with a 5.60 xERA.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Trevor Story** (50.66), who narrowly missed the cut behind **Max Muncy** (52.79) and **Jose Caballero** (51.75). Despite **Trevor Story** having a solid base projection, his score was depressed by a tough matchup against Leahy (3.73 xERA) and neutral platoon splits. Meanwhile, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Josh Naylor** (71.87) as we await official confirmation of his #4 spot; if the lineup shifts, his dynamic platoon advantage could fluctuate. **Jose Caballero** remains a marginal play at 51.75, as his projected efficiency is heavily mitigated by an #8 lineup position and a negative platoon split. With SB being our league's scarcest category, we are prioritizing the volume provided by **Corbin Carroll** and **James Wood** to bridge the gap, while keeping **Austin Riley** and **Zach McKinstry** in reserve as high-upside depth should any last-minute defensive adjustments arise.",
